The "Trump curse" is going to be that we "let Obama go" because we're too scared to administer justice because he's black and we fear a 'race reprisal' and race war, and that will very quickly bring the end of our society.    No justice, no peace.   We are hanging by a thread in this regard already.  Lawlessness is a problem.  We have to adopt a 'let justice be done though the heavens fall" type of approach here.  We need to grow a pair and entertain the idea that black people aren't a monolith, and that those that do get violent, get killed or go to prison--as they should.

Many people have gone to prison for FAR less than what Obama did.  That is not fair.  The perceived unfairness results is more lawlessness.  You see it on the road every day.  People no longer signal when turning or changing lanes.  That's a bellwether of creeping lawlessness.   Its going to get worse the more islamics are dumped into the country, because not only do they not know our laws and rules, they don't care and they are practicing taqiyya which is a clandestine, cultural jihad to transform the country into one that practices sharia law by outcompeting, which means outbreeding.

I think blacks aren't as political as people think; except when it comes to benefits.   I think they'd go much more crazy over SNAP being cut than Obama being arrested.  That's just my opinion, even if i were totally wrong, I still think the country HAS to arrest and prosecute Obama.  For the future of our system.

Get insurance, stay home, arm yourself, and wait it out.  Everything blows over.  Everything.  Worry about what black people will or wont' do is something that should not rule your life.
